df_rent1 <- rent_exclude %>%
  left_join(count(rent_exclude,property_type), by="property_type") %>%
  mutate(prop_type = ifelse((n>100 & !is.na(property_type)),property_type,"Other")) %>%
  subset(select = -c(n,property_type)) %>%
  mutate(bed = ifelse(bed_type == "Studio", 0.5, 
                      ifelse(grepl("+", bed_type, fixed = TRUE),
                      as.integer(substr(bed_type,1,1))+0.5, as.integer(bed_type)))) %>%
  subset(select = -c(bed_type)) %>%
  mutate(sqft = ifelse(!is.na(sqft_min)&sqft_min>0 & !is.na(sqft_min)&sqft_max>0,
                       (sqft_min+sqft_max)/2,
                       ifelse(!is.na(sqft_min)&sqft_min>0, sqft_min,
                              ifelse(!is.na(sqft_max)&sqft_max>0, sqft_max, 
                                     ifelse(sqft>0,sqft,NA))))) %>%
  mutate_at(vars(bed, bathrooms, parking_spots, photo_count, sqft),
            ~ifelse(is.na(.), median(., na.rm = TRUE), .)) %>%
  subset(select = -c(sqft_min, sqft_max)) %>%
  mutate(created_at = lubridate::ymd_hms(created_at))

ttc <- read.csv("ttv_stations.csv")
curr_ttc <- ttc %>%
  filter(status == "current")

calc_mindist <- function(from_lat, from_lon, to_lat_v, to_lon_v) {
  from_lat_r = (from_lat * pi) / 180
  from_lon_r = (from_lon * pi) / 180
  to_lat_r = (to_lat_v * pi) / 180
  to_lon_r = (to_lon_v * pi) / 180
  dlon = to_lon_r - from_lon_r
  dlat = to_lat_r - from_lat_r
  dist = 6371*2*asin(sqrt(sin(dlat/2)^2+
                               cos(from_lat_r)*cos(to_lat_r)*sin(dlon/2)^2))
  return(min(dist))
}

df_rent4$dist_ttc <- mapply(calc_mindist, df_rent4$latitude, df_rent4$longitude,
                            MoreArgs = list(to_lat_v=curr_ttc$lat, to_lon_v=curr_ttc$long))

df_rent4 %>%
  group_by(region) %>%
  summarise(mean_dist = mean(dist_ttc))

df_rent5 <- df_rent4 %>%
  mutate(bathrooms_cap5 = ifelse(bathrooms>5,5,bathrooms),
         sqft_cap4k = ifelse(sqft>4000,4000,sqft),
         photo_cap40 = ifelse(photo_count>40,40,photo_count),
         bed_cap5 = ifelse(bed>5,5,bed))
set.seed(1998)
split_size <- .2
n <- nrow(df_rent5)
# randomly sample the training rows
training_rows <- sample(1:n, size = floor(split_size*n), replace = F)
# the training data
df_rent_train <- df_rent5 %>% 
  slice(training_rows)
# the testing data
df_rent_test <- df_rent5 %>% 
  slice(-training_rows)

# normal model
model <- asking_price ~ bathrooms_cap5 + 
  parking_spots + sqft_cap4k + photo_cap40 + prop_type + bed_cap5 + 
  region + dist_ttc + sqft_cap4k*region + bathrooms_cap5*sqft_cap4k +
  prop_type*sqft_cap4k + bathrooms_cap5*bed_cap5 + 
  bathrooms_cap5*parking_spots + region*dist_ttc +
  region*bed_cap5 
fit <- lm(model , data=df_rent_train)
summary(fit)

# compare the RMSE on test sets for the two models.
rmse <- function(actual, predicted) {
  rmse_val <- sqrt(mean((actual - predicted)^2, na.rm = T))
}

df_sale <- data_sale %>% 
  filter(asking_price >= 100000) %>%
  filter(property_type != "Parking Space")
df_sale1 <- df_sale %>%
  left_join(count(df_sale,property_type), by="property_type") %>%
  mutate(prop_type = ifelse((n>100 & !is.na(property_type)),property_type,"Other")) %>%
  subset(select = -c(n,property_type)) %>%
  mutate(bed = ifelse(bed_type == "Studio", 0.5, 
                      ifelse(grepl("+", bed_type, fixed = TRUE),
                      as.integer(substr(bed_type,1,1))+0.5, as.integer(bed_type)))) %>%
  subset(select = -c(bed_type)) %>%
  mutate(sqft = ifelse(!is.na(sqft) & sqft > 0, sqft, 
                       ifelse(!is.na(sqft_min)&sqft_min>0 & !is.na(sqft_min)&sqft_max>0,
                              (sqft_min+sqft_max)/2,
                              ifelse(!is.na(sqft_min)&sqft_min>0, sqft_min,
                                     ifelse(!is.na(sqft_max)&sqft_max>0, 
                                            sqft_max, NA))))) %>%
  mutate_at(vars(bed, bathrooms, parking_spots, photo_count, sqft),
            ~ifelse(is.na(.), median(., na.rm = TRUE), .)) %>%
  subset(select = -c(sqft_min, sqft_max)) %>%
  mutate(created_at = lubridate::ymd_hms(created_at))

df_sale5 <- df_sale4 %>%
  mutate(bathrooms_cap5 = ifelse(bathrooms>5,5,bathrooms),
         i_bath0 = ifelse(bathrooms == 0, 0, 1),
         sq_park = parking_spots^2,
         sqrt_park = sqrt(parking_spots),
         log_park = log(parking_spots),
         sqft_cap4k = ifelse(sqft>10000,10000,sqft),
         photo_cap40 = ifelse(photo_count>40,40,photo_count)) %>%
  mutate(log_bath5 = log(bathrooms_cap5),
         sqrt_bath5 = sqrt(bathrooms_cap5),
         sq_bath5 = bathrooms_cap5^2,
         log_sqft10k = log(sqft_cap4k),
         sqrt_sqft10k = sqrt(sqft_cap4k),
         sq_sqft10k = sqft_cap4k^2)
set.seed(1998)
split_size <- .2
n <- nrow(df_sale5)
# randomly sample the training rows
training_rows <- sample(1:n, size = floor(split_size*n), replace = F)
# the training data
df_sale_train <- df_sale5 %>% 
  slice(training_rows)
# the testing data
df_sale_test <- df_sale5 %>% 
  slice(-training_rows)

# normal model
model <- asking_price ~ advertise_permission + sqrt_bath5 + 
  sqrt_park + photo_cap40 +
  sqft_cap4k  + prop_type + region + dist_ttc

 # region*bed_cap5 
fit <- lm(model , data=df_sale_train)

# compare the RMSE on test sets for the two models.
rmse <- function(actual, predicted) {
  rmse_val <- sqrt(mean((actual - predicted)^2, na.rm = T))
}

train_rmse <- rmse(df_sale_train$asking_price, predict(fit, df_sale_train))
test_rmse <- rmse(df_sale_test$asking_price, predict(fit, df_sale_test))

train_rmse_log <- rmse(df_sale_train$asking_price, exp(predict(fit_log, df_sale_train)))
test_rmse_log <- rmse(df_sale_test$asking_price, exp(predict(fit_log, df_sale_test)))


summary_results <- tibble(split = c("train", "test"),
                          normal_model = c(train_rmse,test_rmse ),
                          log_model = c(train_rmse_log, test_rmse_log))

DT::datatable(summary_results)
